The paper deals with optimization algorithms for non-convex functions, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses distributed and asynchronous algorithms, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as another likely category. The use of Lyapunov methods and stability analysis suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category. The paper also deals with control theory concepts such as Razumikhin-Lyapunov method, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for optimization, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
